 18 | 
 19 | Native system dialogs for opening and saving files along with message dialogs.
 20 | 
 21 | ## Supported Platforms
 22 | 
 23 | <Compatibility plugin={frontmatter.plugin} />
 24 | 
 25 | ## Setup
 26 | 
 27 | Install the dialog plugin to get started.
 28 | 
 29 | <Tabs>
 30 |     <TabItem label="Automatic">
 31 | 
 32 |         Use your project's package manager to add the dependency:
 33 | 
 34 |         <CommandTabs npm="npm run tauri add dialog"
 35 |                     yarn="yarn run tauri add dialog"
 36 |                     pnpm="pnpm tauri add dialog"
 37 |                     deno="deno task tauri add dialog"
 38 |                     bun="bun tauri add dialog"
 39 |                     cargo="cargo tauri add dialog" />
 40 | 
 41 |     </TabItem>
 42 |     <TabItem label="Manual">
 43 |         <Steps>
 44 | 
 45 |             1. Run the following command in the `src-tauri` folder to add the plugin to the project's dependencies in `Cargo.toml`:
 46 | 
 47 |                 ```sh frame=none
 48 |                 cargo add tauri-plugin-dialog
 49 |                 ```
 50 | 
 51 |             2.  Modify `lib.rs` to initialize the plugin:
 52 | 
 53 |                 ```rust title="src-tauri/src/lib.rs" ins={4}
 54 |                 #[cfg_attr(mobile, tauri::mobile_entry_point)]
 55 |                 pub fn run() {
 56 |                     tauri::Builder::default()
 57 |                         .plugin(tauri_plugin_dialog::init())
 58 |                         .run(tauri::generate_context!())
 59 |                         .expect("error while running tauri application");
 60 |                 }
 61 |                 ```
 62 | 
 63 |             3.  If you'd like create dialogs in JavaScript, install the npm package as well:
 64 | 
 65 |                 <CommandTabs
 66 |                     npm="npm install @tauri-apps/plugin-dialog"
 67 |                     yarn="yarn add @tauri-apps/plugin-dialog"
 68 |                     pnpm="pnpm add @tauri-apps/plugin-dialog"
 69 |                     deno="deno add npm:@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog"
 70 |                     bun="bun add @tauri-apps/plugin-dialog"
 71 |                 />
 72 | 
 73 |         </Steps>
 74 |     </TabItem>
 75 | 
 76 | </Tabs>
 77 | 
 78 | ## Usage
 79 | 
 80 | The dialog plugin is available in both JavaScript and Rust. Here's how you can use it:
 81 | 
 82 | in JavaScript:
 83 | 
 84 | - [Create Yes/No Dialog](#create-yesno-dialog)
 85 | - [Create Ok/Cancel Dialog](#create-okcancel-dialog)
 86 | - [Create Message Dialog](#create-message-dialog)
 87 | - [Open a File Selector Dialog](#open-a-file-selector-dialog)
 88 | - [Save to File Dialog](#save-to-file-dialog)
 89 | 
 90 | in Rust:
 91 | 
 92 | - [Build an Ask Dialog](#build-an-ask-dialog)
 93 | - [Build a Message Dialog](#build-a-message-dialog)
 94 | - [Build a File Selector Dialog](#build-a-file-selector-dialog)
 95 | 
 96 | :::note
 97 | The file dialog APIs returns file system paths on Linux, Windows and macOS.
 98 | 
 99 | On iOS, a `file://<path>` URIs are returned.
100 | 
101 | On Android, [content URIs] are returned.
102 | 
103 | The [filesystem plugin] works with any path format out of the box.
104 | :::
105 | 
106 | ### JavaScript
107 | 
108 | See all [Dialog Options](/reference/javascript/dialog/) at the JavaScript API reference.
109 | 
110 | #### Create Yes/No Dialog
111 | 
112 | Shows a question dialog with `Yes` and `No` buttons.
113 | 
114 | ```javascript
115 | import { ask } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';
116 | // when using `"withGlobalTauri": true`, you may use
117 | // const { ask } = window.__TAURI__.dialog;
118 | 
119 | // Create a Yes/No dialog
120 | const answer = await ask('This action cannot be reverted. Are you sure?', {
121 |   title: 'Tauri',
122 |   kind: 'warning',
123 | });
124 | 
125 | console.log(answer);
126 | // Prints boolean to the console
127 | ```
128 | 
129 | #### Create Ok/Cancel Dialog
130 | 
131 | Shows a question dialog with `Ok` and `Cancel` buttons.
132 | 
133 | ```javascript
134 | import { confirm } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';
135 | // when using `"withGlobalTauri": true`, you may use
136 | // const { confirm } = window.__TAURI__.dialog;
137 | 
138 | // Creates a confirmation Ok/Cancel dialog
139 | const confirmation = await confirm(
140 |   'This action cannot be reverted. Are you sure?',
141 |   { title: 'Tauri', kind: 'warning' }
142 | );
143 | 
144 | console.log(confirmation);
145 | // Prints boolean to the console
146 | ```
147 | 
148 | #### Create Message Dialog
149 | 
150 | Shows a message dialog with an `Ok` button. Keep in mind that if the user closes the dialog it will return `false`.
151 | 
152 | ```javascript
153 | import { message } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';
154 | // when using `"withGlobalTauri": true`, you may use
155 | // const { message } = window.__TAURI__.dialog;
156 | 
157 | // Shows message
158 | await message('File not found', { title: 'Tauri', kind: 'error' });
159 | ```
160 | 
161 | #### Open a File Selector Dialog
162 | 
163 | Open a file/directory selection dialog.
164 | 
165 | The `multiple` option controls whether the dialog allows multiple selection or not, while the `directory`, whether is a directory selection or not.
166 | 
167 | ```javascript
168 | import { open } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';
169 | // when using `"withGlobalTauri": true`, you may use
170 | // const { open } = window.__TAURI__.dialog;
171 | 
172 | // Open a dialog
173 | const file = await open({
174 |   multiple: false,
175 |   directory: false,
176 | });
177 | console.log(file);
178 | // Prints file path or URI
179 | ```
180 | 
181 | #### Save to File Dialog
182 | 
183 | Open a file/directory save dialog.
184 | 
185 | ```javascript
186 | import { save } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog';
187 | // when using `"withGlobalTauri": true`, you may use
188 | // const { save } = window.__TAURI__.dialog;
189 | 
190 | // Prompt to save a 'My Filter' with extension .png or .jpeg
191 | const path = await save({
192 |   filters: [
193 |     {
194 |       name: 'My Filter',
195 |       extensions: ['png', 'jpeg'],
196 |     },
197 |   ],
198 | });
199 | console.log(path);
200 | // Prints the chosen path
201 | ```
202 | 
203 | ---
204 | 
205 | ### Rust
206 | 
207 | Refer to the [Rust API reference](https://docs.rs/tauri-plugin-dialog/) to see all available options.
208 | 
209 | #### Build an Ask Dialog
210 | 
211 | Shows a question dialog with `Absolutely` and `Totally` buttons.
212 | 
213 | ```rust
214 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::{DialogExt, MessageDialogButtons};
215 | 
216 | let answer = app.dialog()
217 |         .message("Tauri is Awesome")
218 |         .title("Tauri is Awesome")
219 |         .buttons(MessageDialogButtons::OkCancelCustom("Absolutely", "Totally"))
220 |         .blocking_show();
221 | ```
222 | 
223 | If you need a non blocking operation you can use `show()` instead:
224 | 
225 | ```rust
226 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::{DialogExt, MessageDialogButtons};
227 | 
228 | app.dialog()
229 |     .message("Tauri is Awesome")
230 |     .title("Tauri is Awesome")
231 |    .buttons(MessageDialogButtons::OkCancelCustom("Absolutely", "Totally"))
232 |     .show(|result| match result {
233 |         true => // do something,
234 |         false =>// do something,
235 |     });
236 | ```
237 | 
238 | #### Build a Message Dialog
239 | 
240 | Shows a message dialog with an `Ok` button. Keep in mind that if the user closes the dialog it will return `false`.
241 | 
242 | ```rust
243 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::{DialogExt, MessageDialogKind};
244 | 
245 | let ans = app.dialog()
246 |     .message("File not found")
247 |     .kind(MessageDialogKind::Error)
248 |     .title("Warning")
249 |     .blocking_show();
250 | ```
251 | 
252 | If you need a non blocking operation you can use `show()` instead:
253 | 
254 | ```rust
255 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::{DialogExt, MessageDialogButtons, MessageDialogKind};
256 | 
257 | app.dialog()
258 |     .message("Tauri is Awesome")
259 |     .kind(MessageDialogKind::Info)
260 |     .title("Information")
261 |     .buttons(MessageDialogButtons::OkCustom("Absolutely"))
262 |     .show(|result| match result {
263 |         true => // do something,
264 |         false => // do something,
265 |     });
266 | ```
267 | 
268 | #### Build a File Selector Dialog
269 | 
270 | #### Pick Files
271 | 
272 | ```rust
273 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::DialogExt;
274 | 
275 | let file_path = app.dialog().file().blocking_pick_file();
276 | // return a file_path `Option`, or `None` if the user closes the dialog
277 | ```
278 | 
279 | If you need a non blocking operation you can use `pick_file()` instead:
280 | 
281 | ```rust
282 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::DialogExt;
283 | 
284 | app.dialog().file().pick_file(|file_path| {
285 |     // return a file_path `Option`, or `None` if the user closes the dialog
286 |     })
287 | ```
288 | 
289 | #### Save Files
290 | 
291 | ```rust
292 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::DialogExt;
293 | 
294 | let file_path = app
295 |     .dialog()
296 |     .file()
297 |     .add_filter("My Filter", &["png", "jpeg"])
298 |     .blocking_save_file();
299 |     // do something with the optional file path here
300 |     // the file path is `None` if the user closed the dialog
301 | ```
302 | 
303 | or, alternatively:
304 | 
305 | ```rust
306 | use tauri_plugin_dialog::DialogExt;
307 | 
308 | app.dialog()
309 |     .file()
310 |     .add_filter("My Filter", &["png", "jpeg"])
311 |     .pick_file(|file_path| {
312 |         // return a file_path `Option`, or `None` if the user closes the dialog
313 |     });
314 | ```
315 | 
