 79 | ## Configuration
 80 | 
 81 | ### Android
 82 | 
 83 | When using the audio, cache, documents, downloads, picture, public or video directories your app must have access to the external storage.
 84 | 
 85 | Include the following permissions to the `manifest` tag in the `gen/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml` file:
 86 | 
 87 | ```xml
 88 | <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"/>
 89 | <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
 90 | ```
 91 | 
 92 | ### iOS
 93 | 
 94 | Apple requires app developers to specify approved reasons for API usage to enhance user privacy.
 95 | 
 96 | You must create a `PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy` file in the `src-tauri/gen/apple` folder
 97 | with the required [NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryFileTimestamp] key and the [C617.1] recommended reason.
 98 | 
 99 | ```xml
100 | <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
101 | <!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
102 | <plist version="1.0">
103 |   <dict>
104 |     <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
105 |     <array>
106 |       <dict>
107 |         <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>
108 |         <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryFileTimestamp</string>
109 |         <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypeReasons</key>
110 |         <array>
111 |           <string>C617.1</string>
112 |         </array>
113 |       </dict>
114 |     </array>
115 |   </dict>
116 | </plist>
117 | ```
