  1 | ---
  2 | title: Notifications
  3 | description: Send native notifications to the user.
  4 | i18nReady: true
  5 | plugin: notification
  6 | ---
  7 | 
  8 | import PluginLinks from '@components/PluginLinks.astro';
  9 | import Compatibility from '@components/plugins/Compatibility.astro';
 10 | import PluginPermissions from '@components/PluginPermissions.astro';
 11 | import { Tabs, TabItem, Steps } from '@astrojs/starlight/components';
 12 | import CommandTabs from '@components/CommandTabs.astro';
 13 | 
 14 | <PluginLinks plugin={frontmatter.plugin} />
 15 | 
 16 | Send native notifications to your user using the notification plugin.
 17 | 
 18 | ## Supported Platforms
 19 | 
 20 | <Compatibility plugin={frontmatter.plugin} />
 21 | 
 22 | ## Setup
 23 | 
 24 | Install the notifications plugin to get started.
 25 | 
 26 | <Tabs>
 27 |     <TabItem label="Automatic">
 28 | 
 29 |         Use your project's package manager to add the dependency:
 30 | 
 31 |         <CommandTabs npm="npm run tauri add notification"
 32 |             yarn="yarn run tauri add notification"
 33 |             pnpm="pnpm tauri add notification"
 34 |             bun="bun tauri add notification"
 35 |         deno="deno task tauri add notification"
 36 |             cargo="cargo tauri add notification" />
 37 | 
 38 | 
 39 |     </TabItem>
 40 |     <TabItem label="Manual">
 41 |         <Steps>
 42 | 
 43 |         1. Run the following command in the `src-tauri` folder to add the plugin to the project's dependencies in `Cargo.toml`:
 44 | 
 45 |            ```sh frame=none
 46 |            cargo add tauri-plugin-notification
 47 |            ```
 48 | 
 49 |         2. Modify `lib.rs` to initialize the plugin:
 50 | 
 51 |            ```rust title="src-tauri/src/lib.rs" ins={4}
 52 |            #[cfg_attr(mobile, tauri::mobile_entry_point)]
 53 |            pub fn run() {
 54 |                tauri::Builder::default()
 55 |                    .plugin(tauri_plugin_notification::init())
 56 |                    .run(tauri::generate_context!())
 57 |                    .expect("error while running tauri application");
 58 |            }
 59 |            ```
 60 | 
 61 |         3. If you'd like to use notifications in JavaScript then install the npm package as well:
 62 | 
 63 | 
 64 |             <CommandTabs
 65 |                 npm="npm install @tauri-apps/plugin-notification"
 66 |                 yarn="yarn add @tauri-apps/plugin-notification"
 67 |                 pnpm="pnpm add @tauri-apps/plugin-notification"
 68 |                 deno="bun add npm:@tauri-apps/plugin-notification"
 69 |                 bun="bun add @tauri-apps/plugin-notification"
 70 |             />
 71 | 
 72 |         </Steps>
 73 |     </TabItem>
 74 | 
 75 | </Tabs>
 76 | 
 77 | ## Usage
 78 | 
 79 | Here are a few examples of how to use the notification plugin:
 80 | 
 81 | - [Send notification to users](#send-notification)
 82 | - [Add an action to a notification](#actions)
 83 | - [Add an attachment to a notification](#attachments)
 84 | - [Send a notification in a specific channel](#channels)
 85 | 
 86 | The notification plugin is available in both JavaScript and Rust.
 87 | 
 88 | ### Send Notification
 89 | 
 90 | Follow these steps to send a notification:
 91 | 
 92 | <Steps>
 93 | 1. Check if permission is granted
 94 | 
 95 | 2. Request permission if not granted
 96 | 
 97 | 3. Send the notification
 98 | 
 99 | </Steps>
100 | 
101 | <Tabs syncKey="lang">
102 | <TabItem label="JavaScript">
103 | 
104 | ```javascript
105 | import {
106 |   isPermissionGranted,
107 |   requestPermission,
108 |   sendNotification,
109 | } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
110 | // when using `"withGlobalTauri": true`, you may use
111 | // const { isPermissionGranted, requestPermission, sendNotification, } = window.__TAURI__.notification;
112 | 
113 | // Do you have permission to send a notification?
114 | let permissionGranted = await isPermissionGranted();
115 | 
116 | // If not we need to request it
117 | if (!permissionGranted) {
118 |   const permission = await requestPermission();
119 |   permissionGranted = permission === 'granted';
120 | }
121 | 
122 | // Once permission has been granted we can send the notification
123 | if (permissionGranted) {
124 |   sendNotification({ title: 'Tauri', body: 'Tauri is awesome!' });
125 | }
126 | ```
127 | 
128 | </TabItem>
129 | <TabItem label="Rust">
130 | 
131 | ```rust
132 | tauri::Builder::default()
133 |     .plugin(tauri_plugin_notification::init())
134 |     .setup(|app| {
135 |         use tauri_plugin_notification::NotificationExt;
136 |         app.notification()
137 |             .builder()
138 |             .title("Tauri")
139 |             .body("Tauri is awesome")
140 |             .show()
141 |             .unwrap();
142 | 
143 |         Ok(())
144 |     })
145 |     .run(tauri::generate_context!())
146 |     .expect("error while running tauri application");
147 | ```
148 | 
149 | </TabItem>
150 | </Tabs>
151 | 
152 | ### Actions
153 | 
154 | :::caution[Mobile Only]
155 | The Actions API is only available on mobile platforms.
156 | :::
157 | 
158 | Actions add interactive buttons and inputs to notifications. Use them to create a responsive experience for your users.
159 | 
160 | #### Register Action Types
161 | 
162 | Register action types to define interactive elements:
163 | 
164 | ```javascript
165 | import { registerActionTypes } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
166 | 
167 | await registerActionTypes([
168 |   {
169 |     id: 'messages',
170 |     actions: [
171 |       {
172 |         id: 'reply',
173 |         title: 'Reply',
174 |         input: true,
175 |         inputButtonTitle: 'Send',
176 |         inputPlaceholder: 'Type your reply...',
177 |       },
178 |       {
179 |         id: 'mark-read',
180 |         title: 'Mark as Read',
181 |         foreground: false,
182 |       },
183 |     ],
184 |   },
185 | ]);
186 | ```
187 | 
188 | #### Action Properties
189 | 
190 | | Property                 | Description                             |
191 | | ------------------------ | --------------------------------------- |
192 | | `id`                     | Unique identifier for the action        |
193 | | `title`                  | Display text for the action button      |
194 | | `requiresAuthentication` | Requires device authentication          |
195 | | `foreground`             | Brings app to foreground when triggered |
196 | | `destructive`            | Shows action in red on iOS              |
197 | | `input`                  | Enables text input                      |
198 | | `inputButtonTitle`       | Text for input submit button            |
199 | | `inputPlaceholder`       | Placeholder text for input field        |
200 | 
201 | #### Listen for Actions
202 | 
203 | Listen to user interactions with notification actions:
204 | 
205 | ```javascript
206 | import { onAction } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
207 | 
208 | await onAction((notification) => {
209 |   console.log('Action performed:', notification);
210 | });
211 | ```
212 | 
213 | ### Attachments
214 | 
215 | Attachments add media content to notifications. Support varies by platform.
216 | 
217 | ```javascript
218 | import { sendNotification } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
219 | 
220 | sendNotification({
221 |   title: 'New Image',
222 |   body: 'Check out this picture',
223 |   attachments: [
224 |     {
225 |       id: 'image-1',
226 |       url: 'asset:///notification-image.jpg',
227 |     },
228 |   ],
229 | });
230 | ```
231 | 
232 | #### Attachment Properties
233 | 
234 | | Property | Description                                    |
235 | | -------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
236 | | `id`     | Unique identifier                              |
237 | | `url`    | Content URL using asset:// or file:// protocol |
238 | 
239 | Note: Test attachments on your target platforms to ensure compatibility.
240 | 
241 | ### Channels
242 | 
243 | Channels organize notifications into categories with different behaviors. While primarily used on Android, they provide a consistent API across platforms.
244 | 
245 | #### Create a Channel
246 | 
247 | ```javascript
248 | import {
249 |   createChannel,
250 |   Importance,
251 |   Visibility,
252 | } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
253 | 
254 | await createChannel({
255 |   id: 'messages',
256 |   name: 'Messages',
257 |   description: 'Notifications for new messages',
258 |   importance: Importance.High,
259 |   visibility: Visibility.Private,
260 |   lights: true,
261 |   lightColor: '#ff0000',
262 |   vibration: true,
263 |   sound: 'notification_sound',
264 | });
265 | ```
266 | 
267 | #### Channel Properties
268 | 
269 | | Property      | Description                                    |
270 | | ------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
271 | | `id`          | Unique identifier                              |
272 | | `name`        | Display name                                   |
273 | | `description` | Purpose description                            |
274 | | `importance`  | Priority level (None, Min, Low, Default, High) |
275 | | `visibility`  | Privacy setting (Secret, Private, Public)      |
276 | | `lights`      | Enable notification LED (Android)              |
277 | | `lightColor`  | LED color (Android)                            |
278 | | `vibration`   | Enable vibrations                              |
279 | | `sound`       | Custom sound filename                          |
280 | 
281 | #### Managing Channels
282 | 
283 | List existing channels:
284 | 
285 | ```javascript
286 | import { channels } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
287 | 
288 | const existingChannels = await channels();
289 | ```
290 | 
291 | Remove a channel:
292 | 
293 | ```javascript
294 | import { removeChannel } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
295 | 
296 | await removeChannel('messages');
297 | ```
298 | 
299 | #### Using Channels
300 | 
301 | Send a notification using a channel:
302 | 
303 | ```javascript
304 | import { sendNotification } from '@tauri-apps/plugin-notification';
305 | 
306 | sendNotification({
307 |   title: 'New Message',
308 |   body: 'You have a new message',
309 |   channelId: 'messages',
310 | });
311 | ```
312 | 
313 | Note: Create channels before sending notifications that reference them. Invalid channel IDs prevent notifications from displaying.
314 | 
315 | ## Security Considerations
316 | 
317 | Aside from normal sanitization procedures of user input there are currently no known security considerations.
318 | 
319 | <PluginPermissions plugin={frontmatter.plugin} />
320 | 


